ROOT CAUSE: two parallel Claude Code sessions both ran `git commit` without
first calling `git status` to verify the index. Pre-staged files from prior
sessions got scooped. The parallel session noted this in its Linear comment
on FFS-1179 and recommended "leave it". I (the Tippy session) concurred
when I found out, because 924bff16 had already been pushed to origin/main
by the time I tried to recover — force-push on pushed main is a protocol
violation and too risky.

FIX FOR FUTURE: Claude Code sessions should ALWAYS run `git status` +
`git diff --cached --stat` immediately before `git commit` and unstage any
unexpected files with `git restore --staged <file>`. Stored as a feedback
memory entry so this doesn't recur.

